description:
Kung Fu Quest

Culture Documentary hosted by Stephen Au and Ka Li and Howard Wen and Philip Ng and Oscar Lam and Kiu Ching Fu and Vinz Sze, published by RTHK in 2011 - Chinese narration


Information
------------------------------

Kung fu has a long history in China. Each school of martial arts has its own profound uniqueness. Over the years, Kung Fu is being featured in literature, drama and film, leading it onto the international scene. Kung Fu is also an entry point of how the western society understands Chinese culture. The hosts of the RTHK;s documentary series &quot;KUNG FU QUEST&quot; interview the grand masters of Wudang, Shaolin, Wing Chun, Hung Kuen and Taichi to deconstruct the unique mystery of each school. Actual combat by the hosts and grand masters are featured in each episode to demonstrate the profundity of Chinese Kung Fu. 
Part 1: At The Apex of Wudang
Part 2: Zen Combatant - Shaolin
Part 3: Wing Chun the Real Art
Part 4: The Authentic Hung Kuen
Part 5: Real combat - Taichi

